In this expression 

    out &lt;&lt; (s.length() &lt; x) &lt;&lt; endl; 

the the variable `x` is converted to the type of std::string::size_type (the type of the expression `s.length()`) due to the usual arithmetic conversion. 

So its value `-100` is converted to some big positive number like `18446744073709551516`.

Try the following demonstrative program

    #include &lt;iostream&gt;
    #include &lt;string&gt;
    
    int main() 
    {
    	std::cout &lt;&lt; std::string::size_type( -100 ) &lt;&lt; &#39;\n&#39;;
    	
    	return 0;
    }

