&gt; But if I perform the function call first and store that in a variable,
&gt; then do the comparison between the variable and the literal, then the
&gt; expression evaluates to false.

then it seems you are doing the following

    int len = s.length();

and then

    out &lt;&lt; (len &lt; x) &lt;&lt; endl; 
\In this case the common type of the operands of the expression `len &lt; x` and there is no conversion of a negative value to an unsigned value.

